cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on using scattering networks as a generic representation for modelling images, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses supervised and unsupervised learning tasks, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of geometrical priors in the small sample regime suggests an interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of GANs to generate images, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
